---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About LogisticsEdge — UK logistics, customs, and supply chain intelligence.">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-header__title">About LogisticsEdge</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        LogisticsEdge provides practical intelligence for UK logistics, customs, and supply chain
        professionals. We cover the topics that matter to people moving goods in and out of the UK
        — from customs compliance and 3PL management to freight operations and trade regulation.
      </p>

      <h2>What we cover</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>UK customs procedures, compliance, and regulatory changes</li>
        <li>Freight and transport operations</li>
        <li>3PL selection, management, and performance</li>
        <li>Supply chain strategy and risk management</li>
        <li>Trade policy and its practical impact on UK logistics</li>
        <li>Tools, technology, and automation in logistics</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why LogisticsEdge</h2>
      <p>
        Most logistics content is either too high-level to be useful or too vendor-driven to be
        trusted. LogisticsEdge is built by practitioners, for practitioners. Every article is
        written with the working logistics professional in mind — the person who needs to know
        what changed, what it means, and what to do about it.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a question, suggestion, or want to contribute? Reach out at
        <a href="mailto:hello@logisticsedge.co.uk">hello@logisticsedge.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
